<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-03T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-03T11:00:00-05:00" n="43" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d43">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/1573:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sterling</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-03T17:00:00+01:00">May 3,
                                        1940—5 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received May 3—3:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>434. From Commercial Attaché.<note n="56" xml:id="d43fn56">George C.
                                    Howard.</note> For our information and to answer repeated
                                inquiries from Swedish firms dependent on American trade we would
                                appreciate advice as to any negotiations undertaken by the
                                Government of the United States looking toward agreements with
                                belligerents to allow resumption of direct trade between the United
                                States and Sweden. Large tractor and other orders awaiting the
                                possibility of import and it has been suggested that Vladivostok and
                                    <pb facs="0070" n="61" xml:id="pg_61"/> trans-Russia route could
                                be utilized and information as to this possibility also urgently
                                needed.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sterling</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>